They have great service and sandwiches! I've ordered to go a few times and they've always been very quick, and the sandwiches very filling with fresh ingredients. My favorite is the roast beef sandwich, which can basically feed 4 people,  you can't go wrong with it.

Hats off to this lot providing quality victuals even during COVID times. Best muffaletta sandwich not from Central Grocery in NO LA. And, God bless them, they gladly customize your order.  If you're in Randolph Corridor just west of Chicago's Loop, ring up JP Graziano for a solid deli luncheon.
Fresh bread, fresh mozzarella , friendly staff, sandwich ALWAYS hits the spot. Honestly, what more could you ask for?

It’s not enough to say this is a great sandwich. This is something more, something above any common use of the word “sandwich.” I believe it is served in heaven.

JPG: I strayed. You were closed. I had a sub called an Italian Sub from a national chain. I thought I had Covid because it had no taste. Bit then I realized: you’ve set the bar so high! I’ll have to buy some meat the next time I’m there- for when your  closed. Much love JPG!

The subs were really tasty. Ordered the Italian, spicy, and turkey sub. Also picked up some mild and hot Giardiniera to go. I did the order online for pick up before I went. There is a window for pick up and ordering. I loved the red roasted pepper on the turkey sub. Gave it an extra kick. I preferred the spicy over the Italian. Both were excellent. The staff was very friendly and appreciative of my business which I liked! This was my first time to JP Graziano‘s and I’m sure not my last.
I love it here. Nothing but enjoyable experiences here. The prices are fair for the quality of food. I see why this place has a lot of positive reviews.

Excellent service.  Super fresh food.  Credit card only.

What a great sandwich. People are really nice also, great service. Highly recommend.
Best place to get a sandwich in Chicago hands down!

We love JP Graziano! Unfortunately, our experience picking up sandwiches the last few months has left a lot to be desired. There’s no system for pickup- you just give your name to the staff member at the door- so people skip ahead in the nonexistent line (clump) and others are left waiting for ages. I think it would benefit everyone if there was a better pickup system. Perhaps the staff member at the door could take multiple names at once instead of bringing sandwiches out one by one, there could be tape on the ground for distancing/queuing purposes, etc. We love the sandwiches but it’s been tough to stand in the sun with a baby for 20 minutes just to pickup an online order.

Great sandwiches.  Deanna is a treasure!
The absolute best sub you will ever eat in your life, cold cuts of amazing flavor, fresh produce, soft spongy bread with an outer crunch, meats of the highest quality.

Good local lunch place. Has an authentic feel to it. Courteous and friendly staff. I ordered a Porchetta and it was served with a humungous Ciabatta bread. The serving here is huge as you can see from the picture. Reach 10 mins before noon to skip the long lunch lines.
The food was great and everyone working there was attentive to us. Very friendly place. I wish I would have known about it sooner.

These have to be the best sandwiches in the city! As a born and raised Chicagoan, I am sad it has taken me nearly 2 decades to find such a treasure. JPG provides nothing but fresh products and flexibility with large orders. I order from them on a weekly basis for corporate lunches at my office since they are in the neighborhood and they're always a hit! People never get sick of their sandwich trays and always prefer the hot giardinara. Thanks for being so reliable, JPG! We are always happy to support a local family business.

This place is very good on their quality of meats and quality of condiments with great prices (about 8.00-10.00 per sandwich). They have a great variety of sandwiches that can satisfy any type of taste buds.  The only issue is the bread is very hard, so biting and chewing into the sandwich will be a problem, and they don't have a wheat or multigrain bread option.  They operate on an honor system when it comes to paying for your meal which can be a problem because after you order your food; you have to go to a separate area to pay for the sandwich and verbally tell the cashier what you ordered.  Normally they give you a ticket of some sort at other deli's, but they don't practice that here; so I would recommend they track their purchases.  Parking here will definitely be a problem, so I highly recommend a car sharing service, taxi or public transportation if you are dining in.  With all that being said; the sandwiches are definitely great and this store is certainly worth dining in at.
One of my favorite places in Chicago!

The staff is friendly, efficient, and authentic. They’ve also got a sandwich punch card where you get a free sub after purchasing 8. I thoroughly endorse!!

perfect sandwich  great price

I had an Artichoke sandwich, which was lovely and large enough to take half home.  We had eaten outside.  When the server saw me wrapping the remaining half in a napkin, she quickly offered to take it in and prep it to go.  We can't wait to eat our way through the rest of the menu!

The best sandwiches.  The Italian with mayo

Great service at this Italian deli! I would recommend these subs to anyone!

After a much anticipated wait I finally had my chance to try out JP Graziano’s. I had to walk for almost about a mile in the cold windy streets of the west loop and all of my efforts and wait were totally going to be worth it. As i reached the store I was greeted with their customary style at the deli counter and at the payment counter, you get a feeling of belongingness and a comfort zone with this place. I decided to go with their famous Mr. G which was quite a big sub for the price. Mr. G has their unique hot oil sauce which has flavours of mustard, balsamic and truffle oil that provide a distinct flavour to the sandwich. The meat is very fresh and the marinated artichoke with lettuce soaked in oregano amd vinegrette would make you crave for more. The basil on top does provide that unique fresh taste and blends well with the entire package. All in all this was one of my best subs in the chicagoland area and does leave a unique flavour for you to remind about what JP Graziano’s is all about.
Awesome upscale convenience store . Fantastic assortment of food, ingredients and beverages that you'd never find in the the average convenience store

Today is my wife's birthday and we drove all the way from Valparaiso Indiana because she wanted to have JP Graziano's and she loved it it was everything that she expected it to be and we're thankful. Highly recommend anyone within any distance take a trip to this wonderful Italian deli.

This place is nothing short of incredible.  The BEST subs in the city without question.  And when you go, do yourself a huge favor and don't remove anything you may not like from a sandwich.  Order it as intended and get everything on it.  This is one of those rare places where they know what you want better than you do.  Trust them and they will not fail you.  In fact, I'm not sure why you're even still reading this.  Go!  Go now!
Great family environment,  awesome subs!!!
Love the Italian subs. Great staff and good food!
The best place for Italian Sandwich. Very friendly staff.
Best Italian sandwiches. Of course, get the Mr G and you won't be disappointed.
Best Italian subs in the west loop. Fresh bread and great sliced meats. Quick and efficient service. Can't go wrong here.

I ordered the prosciutto sandwich and it was superb. The cannoli we ordered was also amazing. The staff had great customer service.
Soooo good
An awesome old scholl deli. The sandwiches and cannolis are beyond compare!
Love this place. Italian family owned deli. Staff is so nice and speedy service is always guaranteed!
Great Italian sandwich with other options. Quick and reasonably priced!
I go almost everyday during lunch at work. A very friendly family owned establishment. Great subs!
Hands down the best Italian sandwich in  Chicago... Period.

Even though it is a small local shop, they offer the best submarine sandwiches during my 7-day Amtrak tour.  I ordered Mr G, Italian and Prosciutto for my Chicago day trip and I loved the Prosciutto the most.  When I told my daughter how good the Prosciutto was, she started buying Prosciutto in NYC.  The best Prosciutto or Jamon  in NYC can cost you $50 a pound.
Great spot for a fresh Italian sandwich! Employees were super friendly and food was awesome. Love how it's family-owned. Three family members working when we went. Must try a cannoli!
Best. Sandwiches. Ever. Welcoming staff treat you like family. Haven't found better subs in Chicago and I've lived downtown for 6 years now.
Wanna get a dope Italian sandwich? Come here. So freaking good!

Nice to get a traditional sub sandwhich every now and again.  This place and bari on Grand avenue are the best in town. This place is truly amazing!!

Very large subs for the price and a wonderful family owned atmosphere. Here's how to order a sandwich for new comers: 1. As you enter stay the the right and get in line by the counter 2. Once acknowledged, give your sandwich order and stay in line 3. Grab extras like drinks and chips as the line moves to the crash register 4. Pay and follow the line back to the front of the store 5. Stay in order and by the time you reach the entrance again your sando will be ready! They'll call you by the sandwich, not name or number.  Enjoy!

I've been coming here for 10 years now and still love it.  Yes the crowds have gotten bad but just come early or late for lunch and you'll be fine.  The owners work here everyday.   This is the real deal classic Italian family run joint.

What a delicious Italian sub I've just had! Graziano's definitely met my expectations based on others' reviews. I can't wait to try the other subs (The veggie really caught my attention)  The service and prompt attention, along with the quality of the food makes Graziano's a must stop while in the West Loop.  Also, for the price, the subs were a lot bigger than I had expected.  I actually had to save half of my sub for later. Which, when thinking about it, means that Graziano's has definitely set me for the day! What a treat!!

Voted one Chicago's Best. In my opinion best sandwiches in the world! Fantastic family run place. Even with lines out the door we received our order in 10 minutes. Must have subs are Tuna and Mr G, though every sub is phenomenal!
VERY FRIENDLY, when I entered. I love subs and I have had them all over. By Far, this place has the best. They even beat the stuffing out of Bari's on Grand Age. Excellent Subs!

I've eaten at a lot of sandwich joints in the area but I've never seen a sandwich wrapped in so much paper like the one I got from these bozos. When I complained about my sandwich being wrapped in, not one, not two, not three, but FOUR jumbo sheets of butcher paper...and a paper bag (even though it was to be eaten in), he looked at me as if I was nuts. The sandwich was tasty but the consumer should be aware of other things about an eating establishment besides the quality of food before patronizing it. These people are criminal wasters - a cancer to our planet. I won't eat there again.

Some of the best sandwiches in the city! I have literally dozens of lunch options a short walk from my office but I make sure to hit JPG every week. Food is delicious and the family that's owned it for generations is awesome.
Not a huge selection, but the quality is high. Picked up some prosciutto which was very well received.
Fantastic consistently delicious sandwiches made fresh.   I'm not a sandwich person, but if I were to have one sandwich for the rest of my life, it would be the Mr. G.

Solid Italian sandwiches. Might not be the best in the city but very close.

Delicious Italian subs that can't be beat elsewhere in the city. This is a go-to where we take out of town guests who want a unique Chicago "institution" experience for the West Loop neighborhood. The spicy and Italian sandwiches are my favorite, but the Mr. G is worth a try for the unique factor. The portions are generous and one sandwich can easily be shared for lunch.

Greatest Italian sub shop in the galaxy. Don't forget to buy a cannoli.  If it's your first time go with one of the prebuilt selections. If you're adventurous build your own. I prefer the proscuitto with extra basil.  Don't miss a chance to do some grocery shopping. Pick up some giardenara, fresh cheese, or if in season wild ramps! All the produce is amazing.
Great family owned Italian deli. Classic Italian sandwiches along with other sandwiches, gelato, and some baked goods. The staff is very friendly and remembers the names of regulars.

Just ordered the 9' Italian sub from Uber EATS... MIND BLOWN.. this is so good and is from a Italian deli that goes back 3 generations in the West Loop. Thanks to the UBER eats I am able to get this ASAP on demand and not travel to enjoy this wonderful sub. A must have and TRY!!!
Best subs.

Great staff and ambiance in this historical Italian deli.  I enjoyed a spicy sub sandwich although the traditional Italian bread could have been a bit lighter.  It was fun to visit this neighborhood staple in the midst of a changing community.

Walked here for lunch while visiting a friend in Chicago. Lots of people came in and out and got sandwiches to-go. I stayed inside to warm up and sat at one of two tables. I ordered the Italian sandwich. It was great, but could've used some hot peppers or giardiniera. I wish I would have added them to my sandwich. The bread was fresh and had a crispy outside but soft inside; perfection! Everyone working there was super friendly and genuinely cared about the food and service they give. They've been open for many, many years and I see why. I'll be back next time I'm in Chicago!

If I could give this 3.5 stars I would. It's better than average but I wasn't as wowed as I thought I would be given the Yelp reviews and the spot on Chicago's Best awhile back.  I grabbed a sandwich to go from JPG's - a prosciutto sandwich specifically. Now, not being a fan of tomatoes, I asked them to substitute giardinere instead. But when I got home and dug in, I didn't really notice it - in fact, I think they forgot it altogether (though the sandwich was sans tomato, which was a good thing!).  The bread was good, the prosciutto could have been a little more robust. I plan to try the place again - I honestly feel a bit like an outcast with the three star review, but I've had better sandwiches at Capri in River Forest, Alpine and Al & Joes.
Gotta love their sandwiches!
This isn't just a great sub place, it's a great restaurant! Such great service and quality ingredients. It's also DELICIOUS!

Every sandwich is great. This is a great place if you're looking for a traditional sub.  I've never been to the shop but my company orders regularly. The Spicy, Italian and Tuna sandwiches are my favorite but all the others are very solid sandwiches.  I'm not sure if it's their own or what brand but they have awesome giardiniera! The closest thing I've had to typical east coast shops I grew up on, which are amazing. Just another prime example that the best food in Chicago is in the near west side.
Unbelievably delicious sandwiches. The Italian or Spicy is the way to go. Without a doubt one of the best sandwiches you can get in Chicago- complete hidden gem.

Jim and the crew know how to do it right in this quaint little Italian deli. Their sandwiches are amazing and the bread is wonderful. There tends to be a small line during lunch, but it's worth the wait. The cannoli are the best I've ever had.
Very friendly family-run place that serves up excellent food (mainly sub sandwiches) at a reasonable price. Can't beat that with a stick.
Fav is the spicy sandwich.

Local, family-owned Italian place. Great customer service and very high-quality products. I bought marscapone, fresh mozzarella, polenta, and olive oil here and was very satisfied with the quality of all.
The BEST
I have been coming here since I was a child and I will never stop going here! The family is always there and so friendly. Best sandwich and best quality Italian Grocery's in town!

Hands down the best place to get an Italian sub.  Not many places where you can shop for imported deli and cheeses while you wait for your sandwich.  Its always a treat for me to go there because I sense the history of the place.  The owners are great and they really do put great care and work into providing quality ingredients and food.   Family owned and in business since 1937, that says plenty.

Yep, it's a five-banger for JPG's.  I waited until I had a bit more experience here before writing anything so I could see if it was consistency or just coincidence that I fell in love with this place the moment I walked through the door.  The "Mr. G." with hot peppers is the way to go, hands down. We ordered something like 20 sandwiches for an office lunch and I'm happy to report a complete success! All sandwiches made properly, all labeled properly, none forgotten nor screwed up. Everyone was quite happy, and very full.
The sandwiches here are amazing, but get here early, during lunch the line is out the door!  Old fashion feel, they really take care of you!
pretty tasty. i highly recommend their original sub the Mr G. I've just gone here once but i'll definitely to go again if i'm in the area.
a hidden gem. Best sandwich shop in town. Only fault is that this place closes way too early. Wish they had one by my house but this place is well worth the drive.

Great mesquite turkey with roasted red peppers and i loe their artichoke sub with fresh mozzarella. They also offer platters and catering for parties and corporate events.

Unbelievable.  I'm not sure what they're putting in their sandwiches, but I can't stop. THEY ARE AMAZING! The ladies behind the register are too sweet for words.  The line was a bit long, but honestly you can't fault them for that.  A+ quality all around

A tad pricey, but you're paying for the quality of meats/cheeses.  Oh, AND you can pick up some groceries while there
